\section{Proposed Method}
This study presents an integrated architecture combining Enterprise Knowledge Graphs (EKG) with an agent-based Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) model to enhance structured retrieval and reasoning beyond conventional vector-based approaches. The system is organized into three functional components: (1) a semantic layer for EKG construction and knowledge modeling, (2) an orchestration layer for agent-based task coordination and query control, and (3) a generative interface layer that integrates RAG with locally deployed language models for grounded natural language interaction. This design which is shown in Figure \ref{fig:framework} enables structured knowledge access, coordinated reasoning, and controlled generative responses within an enterprise information environment. 
