\subsection{The Generative Interface: RAG and Local LLM}
The final component integrates Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with locally deployed Large Language Models (LLMs).
\begin{itemize}
    \item Privacy-First Deployment: To comply with data security and regulatory constraints on sensitive industrial information, open-source LLMs (e.g., Llama 3, Mistral) are deployed in on-premise or private cloud environments, ensuring that proprietary data remains within institutional infrastructure and is not transmitted to external APIs.
\item GraphRAG Mechanism: Structured contextual information from the Enterprise Knowledge Graph (EKG) is provided to the LLM during generation, enabling graph-grounded retrieval and response synthesis. This approach supports context-aware reasoning over domain-specific entities and relations, improving interpretability and response consistency compared to conventional vector-based RAG pipelines.
\end{itemize}
